text.p: Pace bowler Andrew Bichel set up a decisive Sheffield Shield win for Queensland over Victoria on Monday with a career-best 10-wicket match haul.
Bichel took five for 69 to add to his first innings five for 46 as Queensland romped home by eight wickets to stay top of the standings.
Queensland have 18 points from three wins, 10 clear of New South Wales in second place.

Western Australia captain Tom Moody hit 89 not out to help his side to a five-wicket victory over South Australia in Adelaide. Set 285 to win, Western Australia reached the target in the final session.
The triumph was Western Australia's first of the season. South Australia remained bottom with no points.
Tasmania were one wicket from defeat by New South Wales but salvaged a draw in Hobart.
New South Wales declared their second innings on 225 for three after a whirlwind 101 not out by all-rounder Shane Lee.
Tasmania, needing 302 for an unlikely win, reached 268 for nine. Tail-enders Mark Ridgeway and Mark Atkinson successfully withstood the final 14 deliveries.
